cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the decomposition of a monocular color video into direct and indirect illumination components in real-time, which is a problem in computer vision and graphics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization techniques and sparse priors, which are common in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves real-time processing and appearance editing, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.GR (Computer Graphics).
